text.section:
The Advisory Board shall consist of the following individuals:
the Governor or the Governor's designee;
the President of the Senate of Maryland or the President's designee;
the Speaker of the House of Delegates of Maryland or the Speaker's designee;
the State Superintendent of Schools or the Superintendent's designee;
the Secretaries of Health and Mental Hygiene, Juvenile Services, and Human Resources or their designees;
the Special Secretary of the Governor's Office for Children or the Special Secretary's designee;
one representative of the Office of Crime Control and Prevention designated by the Governor; and
seventeen individuals serving 2-year terms, to be appointed by the Governor, as follows:
two members who represent the children's advocacy community;
two members of the after-school provider community who represent providers not included in item (vii) of this item;
two members who are parents of students enrolled in the State in kindergarten through grade 12;
two members who are students enrolled in the State in grades 6 through 12;
one teacher who is working in a school in the State;
one member who represents the statewide network of child care resource and referral centers;
one member who represents the statewide alliance of licensed school age child care providers;
one member of a local management board;
one member of a local board of education;
one member who is a professional in the field of recreation and parks that delivers after-school and summer programs;
one member who represents the concerns of disabled children;
one member who represents the Office of Child Care in the State Department of Education; and
one member who represents the Department of Disabilities.

section.section:
The Executive Committee consists of the following individuals:
the Governor or the Governor's designee;
the Secretary of Human Resources or the Secretary's designee;
the State Superintendent of Schools or the Superintendent's designee;
the Secretary of Juvenile Services or the Secretary's designee;
the Secretary of Health and Mental Hygiene or the Secretary's designee; and
the Special Secretary of the Governor's Office for Children or the Special Secretary's designee.
